You don't have to buy a new DYMO Label maker! â€“Â The label maker has two sliding discs. The top one and the bottom one. There is a "larger space" on the bottom disc where the label maker is supposed to cut the label (scissor icon). If the too discs dislocate, it stops making an imprint on the label. Simply turn the bottom disc back into place (scissor icon, back onto the "larger space" on the lower disc) and it should work again :) â€“Â Happens to me all the time.
